                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "s2_paper_id": "caee3886a23408ca90e37f3b3a40f0a284abb8d1",
                "title": "Common Reference Potetiostat for Reducing Interference in Simultaneous Multi-Technique Electrochemical Arrays",
                "year": 2025,
                "venue": "Italian National Conference on Sensors",
                "citation_count": 0,
                "reference_count": 17,
                "abstract": "Electrochemical sensing enables detection of diverse analytes across multiple sensing domains. While microfluidic platforms and microelectrode arrays have advanced multi-analyte detection, most rely on time-division multiplexing, limiting true simultaneous, multi-technique measurements from extracting the full capability of multi-analyte sensing. This work identifies limitations in conventional potentiostat designs for microfluidic microelectrode arrays and demonstrates that a novel potentiostat topology reduces the amount of measurement interference from these limitations. Experimental results demonstrate reduced interference and improved system stability for our alternative potentiostat design, supporting reliable, simultaneous, multi-technique operation in microfluidic and arrayed electrochemical systems.",
